Machine Learning & Deep Learning Projects (Data 188, UC Berkeley)
Built end-to-end deep learning pipelines in PyTorch, including data loading, model training, evaluation, and performance tracking for image classification tasks.
Implemented a two-layer neural network from scratch (NumPy + autograd-style logic), including forward pass, backpropagation, and stochastic gradient descent optimization.
Designed and trained multilayer perceptron (MLP) classifiers on Fashion-MNIST and CIFAR-10, achieving competitive accuracy benchmarks (~40% on CIFAR-10).
Developed a modular training framework with custom train_epoch and test loops, including throughput tracking, logging, and evaluation metrics (accuracy, loss).
Built a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) with residual connections, including custom Conv blocks (Conv → BatchNorm → ReLU) and skip connections inspired by ResNet architectures.
Applied adaptive pooling and architectural design principles to handle variable spatial dimensions and optimize model performance.
Debugged and optimized models for correctness and efficiency, including parameter validation, memory management (e.g., .item() usage), and device-aware training (CPU/GPU).
